 dispell, though it really wasn't a threat in toe-to-toe as neither of us have a channeling skill. Then I drank one charge of my level/4 DS potion, the cheap kind. I guess he didn't have anything to click ready aside from his epic. Anyway, we were just starting to duel when I pulled out my last trick... I landed Walking Sleep on him (on the 3rd attempt :/ ) with my Midnight Mallet. That did him in, Mend and Discipline couldn't save him. I ended the fight with a tiny bit less than 2 red bubs of health.<br><br>We're friends though, so I offered him a rematch on a more level playing field. We haven't talked specifics yet, but it'll be in a place where he can run around freely... and I'm sure he'll be better prepared... so I have a few questions if any of you have experience with Monk/Warrior duels. BTW, neither of us are to level or gain aaxp. Some basics first:<br><br>His DPS (slowed remember) was 15.58<br>My DPS was 14.98<br><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=19091">His Stuff</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=10201">My Stuff</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>Things I did wrong:<br>A. Chardok ring wasn't charged, lost 25pts of DS there.<br>B. Discipline wasn't up, was 90 seconds away from getting it back when the fight ended.<br>C. (oops) Used Gauntlets of the Black instead of Blood Runed Gauntlets.<br>D. (oops) Used Shainai's Nightie (was showing off) for much of the fight instead of Berserker's BP.<br>E. Forgot to use my stat food (+3 str/sta).<br>F. Hadn't picked up the Frostbringer I'm buying.<br><br>Keeping in mind that he'll be mobile and prepared in the next duel, here are the questions flooding my mind:<br>1. I'm not sure what discipline he used, but the text was &quot;Whorl's face becomes twisted with fury.&quot; What discipline is that and do you think he'd use it again?<br>2. Cleric buffs. Do they work to my advantage or his in a prepared fight?<br>3. Snare kiting. Should I bother to wait for a proc and hope one lands just so I can run around throwing javelins or shooting arrows at him?<br>4. Which discipline should I use? Defensive? Evasive? Charge? Might Strike when berserk?<br>5. What clicky or worn effect items can I get to help me out? Either ones that harm him or buff me. I will be camping Shrunken Goblin Earring. Was thinking maybe a regen item (fungi is out of reach) and trying to complete my spirit wracked cords quest (just need urn from HS) for an Aura of Battle effect. That Dragon Tooth Choker he's wearing looks good too. We both have charged Root items. I also seem to remember an OLD spear that has a few charges of clickable haste.<br>6. I'm not really looking into upgrading my main gear for the fight because I'm broke and there's not much I can camp quickly. If you see anything in the range of 10k (I can try to raise that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) that would *really* help me out, please say so though.<br>7. How can I expect this fight to go? I've dueled him now and a Druid (indoor, he was hitting on my wife in Thurg hehe) once before him. I won both, but I'm still inexperienced. He's really a great monk, I just always keep those toys on me for mob encounters.<br>8. Any other info you think would help me. I'm really starting to like dueling and the preparation is very exciting too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><p align="center"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=10201"><img border="0" src="http://www.go56.com/xj/XorizTMNT.jpg" width="272" height="186"></a><br><font color="#00FF00">Baron Xoriz Jebekis, level 55 Iksar Warrior</font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left>