F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=remfdatroll>Remf da Troll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 124<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/24/02 10:52:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1463.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dueling a monk (looking for rematch tips)</span><hr size=1> mmmmm.... warrior pvp. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Just some ideas for easy to get items/basic tactics:<br>-holgresh mojo sticks from waking land; 5ch, targetable, right click nukes for 100-200pts.<br>-deathbeetle gland from sol b *grin*<br>-tss whip from TOFS (poison based snare)<br>-easy quest weapon from seru that proc's disempower (mini cripple).<br>-if you are a large race warrior, a weighted axe is THE uber dueling weapon.  Regular hit for 300+, have had crips for over 1k. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>-sow/lev/invis all good for outdoor fights<br>-10 ch ice giant toe potions from shaman = 3000hp (evens up his mend quite nicely).<br>-good bow + high damage/range arrows, or a tink bag or two full of throwing boulders can do NICE damage while jousting.<br>-forlorn totems from stonebrunt = stun + 50ish DD, right click.<br>-have your MR over 100ish and his click snares shouldn't stick much; consider shammy potions if your gear doesn't allow that.<br>-PRACTICE JOUSTING.  You want to hit him from BEHIND if you can, since his oober avoidance skills won't work then.  Takes a LOT of practice to get this right.<br>-make a &quot;faux&quot; furious message, use it whenever he tries to fight you face to face.  Eventually he'll figure it out, then use the real thing on him. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>-get another level or two done; level makes a HUGE difference in damage output.  He probably did more dmg to himself on your DS than you did to him if he outleveled you by that much. :/<br><br>Have fun. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>RdT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uulua55.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ulua55</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://fiftheclipse.wwm.net/sigs/pala2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/25/02 1:14:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1463.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dueling a monk (looking for rematch tips)</span><hr size=1> One of my favorite tricks while dueling a monk is to sucker them in close and autorip with a high damage 2H weapon. Using Tantor's tusk long ago I did about 1k dmg to a monk in a duel in one round. Expect them to back off when they see the disc fire and be ready to chase. Hopefully you will get a some good ripostes in before he turns off attack. <p>Ulua O'Maui Level 60 Woodelf Warrior of Arete, E'ci Server<br><IMG SRC="http://liquid2k.com/shooto/bigsmile.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugalarianizuber.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galarian iz uber</A>&nbsp; <IMG